<taxonomicName authorityName="Uhler" authorityYear="1894" box="[979,1193,592,616]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="994" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[979,1193,592,616]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="994">Microvelia longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably the most
</emphasis>
easily identified Neotropical species of the genus. Males have strikingly long hind legs that are much longer than the body. Female hind legs reach at least the apex of the abdomen and are very long compared to other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1834" box="[846,962,759,783]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="994" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
